# Vercel — Solvio project only

Use the **Vercel CLI** for env vars, deploys, and inspection on this repo. The user is logged in locally (`vercel whoami`); no token required unless CI.

## Correct project (never Tipsi)

Always operate on the linked **solvio** project:

| Field | Value |
|-------|--------|
| Project name | `solvio` |
| Project ID | `prj_lxbtbFAzyGxvITJBaKga2eFqeT7P` |
| Team / scope | `mattyg1234s-projects` (`team_JRCtlld9iiMiuBw5kyLcfF7m`) |
| Link file | `.vercel/project.json` |

**Do not** deploy or set env vars on: `tipsi`, `tipsi2-0`, `tipsi-upgrade`, `v0-solvio`, or other team projects.

Before any `vercel env` or `vercel deploy`, confirm cwd is `Village/sites/solvio` and `cat .vercel/project.json` shows `projectName: solvio`.

## Production URLs

- Canonical: `https://www.solviosystems.com`
- Vercel alias: `https://solvio-roan.vercel.app`

Stripe webhook endpoint: `https://www.solviosystems.com/api/webhooks/stripe`

## Common commands

```bash
cd Village/sites/solvio
npx vercel env ls production
printf '%s' 'value' | npx vercel env update VAR_NAME production -y --sensitive
npx vercel deploy --prod --yes
npx vercel inspect <deployment-url>
```

After changing Production env vars, **redeploy production** so serverless functions pick up new values.
